def save2csv(df, ticker):
    '''save quandl file to csv for later use'''
    
    datum = '{:{dfmt}}'.format(datetime.datetime.now(), dfmt='%Y-%m-%d')
    filename = datum +"_" + ticker.replace("/","_") + ".csv"
    df.to_csv(filename)
In [3]:
def clean_data(df):
    
    '''Returns dataframe with 0 replaced by previous value'''
    
    cols = df.columns
    df_cleaned = pd.DataFrame()
    for col in cols:
        df_cleaned[col] = df[col].replace(to_replace=0, method = "ffill")

    return df_cleaned
In [4]:
def plot_verteilungen(rets_art, rets_log):
    
    '''Returns plot with Verteilung und QQ-Plot von rets_art und rets_log'''

    ## Plotte Renditen zum Vergleich
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=2, figsize = (9,7), dpi = 100, sharex = "col")
    axes = [el for ax in axes for el in ax]

    ## Plot1 Verteilung rets_art
    ax = axes[0]
    _ = rets_art.plot(kind = "hist", ax = ax)
    ax.set_title("Verteilung - Arithmetische Renditen")
    ## Plot2 QQ-Plot rets_art
    ax = axes[1]
    _ = stats.probplot(rets_art, dist="norm", plot=ax)
    ax.set_title("QQ-Plot - Arithmetische Renditen")
    ## Plot3 Verteilung rets_log
    ax = axes[2]
    _ = rets_log.plot(kind = "hist", ax = ax)
    ax.set_title("Verteilung - Logarithmierte Renditen")
    ax.set_xlim(min(rets_log),max(rets_log))
    ## Plot4 QQ-Plot rets_art
    ax = axes[3]
    _ = stats.probplot(rets_log, dist="norm", plot=ax)
    ax.set_title("QQ-Plot - Logarithmierte Renditen")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.suptitle("Vergleich - historischer BitCoin-Renditen", y = 1.025)

Step 3: Calculate returns

Note: use "close" prices for return calculation

In [7]:
## Calculate discrete and log returns
rets_art = df_cleaned["Close"] / df_cleaned["Close"].shift(1) -1 # Arithmetische Renditen
rets_log = np.log(df_cleaned["Close"]) - np.log(df_cleaned["Close"].shift(1)) # Logarithmierte Renditen

## Delete outliers
lbound_art, ubound_art = rets_art.quantile(0.01), rets_art.quantile(0.99)
lbound_log, ubound_log = rets_log.quantile(0.01), rets_log.quantile(0.99)
rets_art = rets_art[(rets_art > lbound_art) & (rets_art < ubound_art)]
rets_log = rets_log[(rets_log > lbound_log) & (rets_log < ubound_log)]

## Plote Verteilung und QQ-Plot fr Renditen
plot_verteilungen(rets_art, rets_log)

# create and fit the LSTM network
model = Sequential()
model.add(LSTM(4, input_shape=(1, 1)))
model.add(Dense(1))
model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
lstm = model.fit(trainX, trainY, epochs=10, batch_size=1, verbose=2)
